commit.message:
Added upload parts from CSV and gzip files

Some of these functions can probably be combined. One reads a normal CSV file and streams it to Domo. Another reads a normal CSV, compresses it to gzip, and then uploads it to Domo (I am not sure if this would increase speed or reduce network requirements). And finally, one function reads a gzip file and uploads gzip parts to Domo.

commit.message:
Add functions to upload gzip files

This uses zlib.compress() to compress the CSV before sending it to Domo.

Note - since I use csv.read(), this could potentially use a lot of memory. Not certain if there is a better way to do this.

commit.message:
Add upload_part_from_file and gzip

This is modeled after the dataset import_from_file function.
It seems like the API has support for this already, but I did not see anything within the StreamClient:
https://developer.domo.com/docs/stream/upload-in-parallel 

I tested this on a few files with about 1 million rows per part and it was much faster than my previous process of querying data to StringIO (limited number of rows due to memory constraints) and sending parts in a loop.
